## 2026-04-03 - SelectionInspector disables token binding when multi-selection has mixed values
- Removed `!isMixed` from the `canBind` guard in `PropertyRow.tsx`. The condition `const canBind = !isBound && !isMixed && ...` prevented the bind button from appearing when multiple selected nodes had different values for a property. The fix allows binding even with mixed values — `handleBindToken` in `SelectionInspector.tsx` already sends `apply-to-selection` to all selected nodes, so the bind correctly unifies all nodes under the chosen token.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/PropertyRow.tsx` ~L98
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

